cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper discusses the use of random feature maps for object classification, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of nonlinear kernels and the reduction of training and testing time, which are topics commonly discussed in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework using two databases, which falls under the sub-category cs.SD (Sound).
